<p class="block-text">Imagine that you are at a party at Debby's
house. You enter the kitchen and overhear something that Debby says
about a person at the party.

<br>
<br> For example, Debby says: <i> Jill is annoyed that <u>her stylist has green hair</u>. </i>

<br>
<br>
We ask you to judge whether Debby thinks that the underlined part of
her utterance is true: <b> Does Debby think that it is true that
Jill's stylist has green hair? </b>

<br>
<br>
You indicate your answer on the following scale, ranging from "No, not true" to "Yes, true":
</p>

